Chapter 5: Strengthen Conflict and Repair
Core Question
Can we stay organized when disagreement appears?
Understand
Conflict does not automatically destroy a society.
Unstructured conflict does.
Every serious society needs a repair process.
Repair protects the work from silence, resentment, gossip, domination, avoidance, and public collapse.
A repair process should include:
How concerns are raised
 Who receives them
 What timeline exists
 What privacy applies
 What meeting or conversation happens
 What record is kept
 What decision is made
 What follow-up occurs
 What happens if repair fails
Repair does not mean every relationship becomes close.
It means conflict does not destroy the room.
Discuss
How do we currently handle disagreement?
What conflict pattern could harm the society?
What should never happen in conflict?
Who can help facilitate repair?
What record should be kept without exposing private details?
