Chapter 6: New Member Orientation
Core Question
How do people enter without weakening the culture?
Understand
Growth should not dilute the society.
New members need orientation before access to responsibility.
Membership is not just joining a list.
Membership means understanding:
Purpose
 Covenant
 Contribution rhythm
 Privacy expectations
 Meeting rhythm
 Treasury basics
 Aid rules
 Care team roles
 Conflict process
 History of the society
 Current phase
 What is expected
 What is not promised
New members should know they are joining a structure, not a vibe.
Orientation protects the society from confusion and protects new members from unclear expectations.
Discuss
Who should be invited next?
What must every new member understand?
What should new members not access immediately?
What expectations must be clear before membership is accepted?
How do we distinguish members from supporters?
