PART THREE: TRAIN AND ROTATE LEADERSHIP

Chapter 7: Build the Leadership Bench
Core Question
Who is being trained to carry the work next?
Understand
A society becomes an institution when leadership is not trapped in one person.
The leadership bench is the group of people being trained to carry roles.
A bench does not appear automatically.
It must be built intentionally.
Every key role should have:
Current lead
 Backup
 Trainee
 Written procedure
 Practice opportunity
 Review date
The founder should not be the only person who knows what is happening.
The treasurer should not be the only person who understands money.
The recordkeeper should not be the only person who knows where memory lives.
The care coordinator should not be the only person who knows who needs help.
Institutions train replacements before replacement is needed.
Discuss
Which role would hurt the society most if the person disappeared?
Who is ready to learn?
Who needs mentoring?
What role should rotate first?
What procedure must be written before training starts?
