Chapter 8: Rotate Without Breaking Trust
Core Question
How do we share power without creating confusion?
Understand
Role rotation keeps the society healthy.
But rotation without preparation can create confusion.
Rotation should be planned, documented, and supported.
A role rotation should include:
Outgoing person
 Incoming person
 Shadow period
 Training notes
 Access transfer
 Open tasks
 Risks
 Review date
Power should not become permanent by accident.
But responsibility should not be handed off casually.
Rotation teaches the society that the work belongs to the institution, not one person.
Discuss
Which role is ready to rotate?
Which role is too sensitive to rotate quickly?
What access needs to transfer?
What knowledge needs to be documented?
What support does the incoming person need?
Build: Role Rotation Plan
