Chapter 11: Partnership Standards
Core Question
Who can we partner with without being extracted?
Understand
As the society becomes visible, partners may appear.
Some partners will be helpful.
Some will be extractive.
A partnership should strengthen the society’s purpose, not redirect it.
Before accepting partnership, ask:
Does this align with our purpose?
 What do they want from us?
 What do we receive?
 What do members risk?
 Who controls the story?
 Who controls the data?
 Who controls the money?
 Can we say no later?
 Is this written clearly?
Visibility is not the same as power.
A society should not trade control for attention.
Discuss
What partnerships would help us?
What partnerships would extract from us?
What should we never give away?
Who approves partnerships?
What must be written before partnership begins?
