Chapter 12: Legal and Formal Structure Check
Core Question
Do we need formal structure now?
Understand
Not every society needs immediate legal formation.
But as money, membership, public activity, property, partnerships, or liability increase, the society should consider whether formal structure is needed.
This may include:
Fiscal sponsorship
 Nonprofit formation
 Cooperative structure
 LLC
 Unincorporated association agreement
 Community fund structure
 Formal bank account
 Insurance
 Legal counsel
 Accounting support
 Data protection policies
This handbook does not provide legal advice.
It helps the society recognize when professional guidance may be needed.
Formal structure should serve the mission.
It should not replace trust.
Discuss
Are we handling enough money to need formal review?
Are we signing agreements?
Are we serving the public?
Are we taking on liability?
Are we storing sensitive data?
Are we considering property?
Do we need legal or accounting guidance?
Build: Formal Structure Readiness Check
