PART FIVE: MEASURE MATURITY

Chapter 13: Institution Maturity Audit
Core Question
Are we becoming more durable?
Understand
Do not measure only activity.
Measure institution-building.
A busy society can still be fragile.
A quieter society can be strong if it has trust, roles, records, rules, repair, treasury discipline, leadership development, and reporting.
Institution maturity asks:
Can we repeat this?
 Can we teach this?
 Can we survive transition?
 Can we protect trust?
 Can we handle money?
 Can we repair conflict?
 Can we train youth?
 Can we protect elders?
 Can we support businesses responsibly?
 Can we steward property carefully?
 Can we report honestly?
